Methods in net.sf.openrds with parameters of type Requisition
 void IMainNode.processAsyncRequisition(Requisition requisition)
          Adds the given requisition to be processed asynchronously.
Warning: using this method won't give you any result, even if the requisition fails to process by any reason.
 java.lang.Object INode.processRequisition(Requisition requisition)
          Process the given requisition and returns it's result.
Note that the behavior of this method beeing called on a MainNode is to look for an available ProcessNode and repass the requisition to it.
 void INodeEventListener.nodeRequisitionProcessed(INode node, Requisition requisition, java.lang.Object result)
          Called when a node finishs processing a requisition with success.
IMPORTANT: On IMainNode this works only when calling IMainNode.processRequisition() and not when calling IMainNode.processAsyncRequisition()
 void INodeEventListener.nodeRequisitionFailed(INode node, Requisition requisition, java.lang.Throwable error)
          Called when a node fails to process a requisition.
